There's a difference between one line and short/terse/elegant.<p><pre><code>  {m:(x,x)#til x*x; r:til[x]-x div 2; 2(flip r rotate')/m} 
</code></pre>
generates magic squares of odd size, and the method is much clearer. This isn't even golfed as the variables have been left.

